`php
public function count(boolean $count = true) throws IGDBInvalidArgumentException: IGDBQueryBuilder
`

This method will accept a boolean value. This parameter is processed in case of a multiquery build only. If this value is true the response from IGDB will contain the number of records matching the filters. If false the records will be returned.If the method is called without parameters, the value will be set to true.

Default value: by default this value is false, the queries will return the records instead of their count.

Parameters:
 $count: true if a record count is required, false otherwise.

Returns: IGDBQueryBuilder instance

